{
  "stem": "13457.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Anyway, the-- the man-- the-- the British government allowed these 3,000 Jews to come from Tehran on a transport and go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we went through Suez.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we arrived in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This, incidentally, [? began ?] [? travel ?] [? as ?] my father through Iraq, and also to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he dropped out from the Polish Army and went into underground.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 11 SECONDS] Then in Israel, we started a new life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now, looking backwards, in terms of numbers, the 3,000 Jews that came from Persia, I think they were the only Jews, maybe few hundred here and there, that came to Palestine throughout the war. '30-- in 1939, when we left Poland and went into Russia, there was 300,000 Jews that escaped that way from Germans.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But then a lot of them, prior to '41, returned back to-- to-- to Germany, or to Warsaw or to German-occupied areas, since the life under Soviet rule wasn't that good either.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In other words, the shipments to Siberia and such scared some people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they returned to Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And obviously, most of them perished.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And these that got out from Russia, there were just 3,000 of us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the rest stayed in-- in-- in Russia, whatever the correct number is.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And-- and returned-- some of them returned to Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And that's it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's basically the end of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know whether I should go to my life in-- in-- in pre-Israel Palestine and Israel itself.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Should I or shouldn't I?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'd-- I'd like to--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Only briefly.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'd-- I'd like to maybe go-- go back to Persia.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Did the camp have a specific name?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The refugee camp?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just numbers.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And camp number one, number two, and number three.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
